export let _markdown = "\n\n## Frequently Asked Questions\n\n### General Questions\n\n#### What is Chr3D?\n\nChr3D is a unified Python ecosystem for analyzing 3D chromatin conformation data from Hi-C, ChIA-PET, and HiChIP experiments.\n\n#### How do I install Chr3D?\n\n```bash\npip install chr3d\n```\n\n#### Which protocols does Chr3D support?\n\nChr3D supports Hi-C, ChIA-PET, and HiChIP with a unified API.\n\n### Analysis Questions\n\n#### What resolution should I use?\n\n* **5kb:** High-resolution (requires >1B reads)\n* **10kb:** Standard analysis (requires >500M reads)\n* **25kb:** TADs and compartments (requires >200M reads)\n\n#### How do I call loops?\n\n```python\nfrom chr3d import HiC\n\nhic = HiC.from_cooler(\"sample.cool\")\nhic_norm = hic.normalize(method=\"ICE\")\nloops = hic_norm.call_loops(method=\"hiccups\", fdr=0.1)\n```\n\n### Quality Control\n\n#### What QC metrics should I check?\n\n* Valid pairs percentage\n* Cis/Trans ratio\n* Library complexity\n* Protocol-specific metrics (linker efficiency for ChIA-PET, enrichment for HiChIP)\n\n### Getting Help\n\nFor more detailed information, see the [Tutorials](./tutorials) and [Guides](./guides) sections.\n";
